00:57:47,014 --> 00:57:49,838
What are you talking about?
Of course I want to see you.

724
00:57:50,384 --> 00:57:52,101
Right, whatever.

725
00:57:55,322 --> 00:57:58,258
I better get back to work
before my boss has a cow.

726
00:57:58,358 --> 00:57:59,775
Yeah.

727
00:58:11,287 --> 00:58:15,392
I am so sorry that I'm late.
Traffic was ridiculous.

728
00:58:15,492 --> 00:58:17,944
No problem, sweetheart.

729
00:58:18,295 --> 00:58:21,114
Kat, this is May. May, Kat.

730
00:58:21,214 --> 00:58:23,233
I'm so happy we finally
get the chance to meet.

731
00:58:23,333 --> 00:58:26,737
- I've heard so much about you.
- Oh, me too.

732
00:58:28,088 --> 00:58:31,124
And you're even lovelier
than your father described.

733
00:58:31,224 --> 00:58:33,727
I'm sure that's not true,
but thank you anyway.

734
00:58:33,877 --> 00:58:36,096
So how long will you
be in town, Katrina?

735
00:58:36,346 --> 00:58:39,900
Oh, just a week.
Then it's back to the salt mines.

736
00:58:40,000 --> 00:58:44,354
- Kat got almost all "A" s her first semester.
- Wow, congratulations.

737
00:58:44,454 --> 00:58:48,225
Yeah. I lucked out. Have you
guys ordered yet? I'm starved.

738
00:58:48,325 --> 00:58:50,772
Your favourite, the spinach artichoke
appetiser. It's already on its way.

739
00:58:50,872 --> 00:58:52,279
Oh, yes.

740
00:58:52,379 --> 00:58:55,671
I'm going to make a quick trip to
the ladies room. If the waiter comes,

741
00:58:55,771 --> 00:58:58,550
- you know what I want.
- Right, okay.

742
00:59:06,993 --> 00:59:08,518
So...

743
00:59:09,084 --> 00:59:13,650
- Are you all right with this?
- What? You mean May?

744
00:59:14,101 --> 00:59:17,054
Yeah, Dad I like her. She seems sweet.

745
00:59:17,254 --> 00:59:19,156
I just don't want it
to be awkward for you.

746
00:59:19,256 --> 00:59:21,892
Dad, I told you I am thrilled
that you met someone.

747
00:59:21,992 --> 00:59:24,593
Seriously, you deserve to be happy.

748
00:59:29,866 --> 00:59:32,053
Took off your wedding ring.

749
00:59:35,172 --> 00:59:38,258
It makes May uncomfortable.

750
00:59:38,358 --> 00:59:41,100
I put it back on when she's not around.

751
00:59:41,411 --> 00:59:44,120
Why bother? I mean, mom left us.

752
00:59:44,220 --> 00:59:47,633
She's the one who made that choice.
I accept that now.

753
00:59:48,483 --> 00:59:51,593
It's about time we
get on with our lives.

754
01:00:03,934 --> 01:00:05,434
Mom?

755
01:00:09,022 --> 01:00:10,727
Kat.

756
01:00:10,827 --> 01:00:12,758
What is it? What's wrong?

757
01:00:13,709 --> 01:00:18,161
I put my hands in the water,
and they disappeared.

758
01:00:18,964 --> 01:00:20,502
What?

759
01:00:22,417 --> 01:00:27,318
I was doing the dishes
and the water was so cold.

760
01:00:27,907 --> 01:00:31,404
There was a spoon at the
bottom of the sink, and...

761
01:00:31,504 --> 01:00:35,497
when I lifted my hands out of the water...

762
01:00:48,128 --> 01:00:49,984
What's the matter?

763
01:00:50,190 --> 01:00:51,956
Nothing.

764
01:00:53,865 --> 01:00:56,928
Just have strange dreams sometimes.

765
01:00:59,020 --> 01:01:00,654
Oh, yeah?

766
01:01:01,574 --> 01:01:03,312
Yeah.

767
01:01:04,893 --> 01:01:07,644
They started after
my mother disappeared.

768
01:01:07,981 --> 01:01:12,783
Used to get them all the time. It's actually
the first one I've had in weeks.

769
01:01:14,086 --> 01:01:16,723
Hardly ever talk about your mother.

770
01:01:16,823 --> 01:01:20,174
There's not much to say. She's gone.

771
01:01:21,976 --> 01:01:24,994
The shrink says dreams are meaningless.

772
01:01:26,614 --> 01:01:28,515
I don't think I agree with that.

773
01:01:31,035 --> 01:01:33,836
What do you think my dreams mean?

774
01:01:43,900 --> 01:01:47,870
- You really want my opinion?
- Of course. Why wouldn't I?

775
01:01:54,027 --> 01:01:56,997
As you know, we did an
exhaustive search for your mother.

776
01:01:57,097 --> 01:02:00,250
Exhaustive? You guys
barely even looked for her.

777
01:02:00,350 --> 01:02:04,087
Actually, a very thorough
investigation was done.

778
01:02:04,187 --> 01:02:06,756
We spent over two years
looking for your mom.

779
01:02:06,956 --> 01:02:10,645
Not a single trace was ever found.

780
01:02:11,672 --> 01:02:13,431
Whatever.

781
01:02:14,763 --> 01:02:16,997
So where do you think she is?

782
01:02:20,503 --> 01:02:22,462
I think she's dead.

783
01:02:25,239 --> 01:02:26,860
What?

784
01:02:27,511 --> 01:02:30,784
Well, you said yourself
she was having an affair,

785
01:02:30,884 --> 01:02:34,393
which we confirmed. With your neighbour,

786
01:02:34,493 --> 01:02:37,254
- Mrs. Blangman?
- Mrs. Hillman.

787
01:02:38,455 --> 01:02:42,771
Whatever. She said...
your mom had a boyfriend.

788
01:02:43,125 --> 01:02:44,123
How would she know?

789
01:02:45,277 --> 01:02:49,098
- She's nosey.
- She can't see.

790
01:02:53,303 --> 01:02:56,139
Wait... whatever. Even if my
mom did have a boyfriend,

791
01:02:56,239 --> 01:03:00,359
doesn't it just make it that much more
likely that she just ran off somewhere?

792
01:03:05,365 --> 01:03:06,955
What?

793
01:03:08,151 --> 01:03:11,134
What? What is it?
What aren't you saying?

794
01:03:12,970 --> 01:03:16,126
We did a thorough background
check on your father.

795
01:03:16,226 --> 01:03:19,318
Several interviewees told us

796
01:03:19,418 --> 01:03:22,899
that he was a pretty
jealous and volatile man.

797
01:03:22,999 --> 01:03:25,968
My dad is a fucking wimp.

798
01:03:26,169 --> 01:03:28,221
That's why he used
to drive my mom crazy.

799
01:03:28,321 --> 01:03:31,913
- Not according to Bob and Margie Carlsen.
- Who are they?

800
01:03:32,063 --> 01:03:36,479
Your former neighbours. Your parents used
to live next door to them in Riverside.

801
01:03:36,579 --> 01:03:39,322
They told us that when
your father suspected

802
01:03:39,422 --> 01:03:42,525
your mother had a thing for Bob Carlsen,

803
01:03:43,325 --> 01:03:47,654
he lit a trash can on fire and
he tossed it onto their patio.

804
01:03:50,074 --> 01:03:52,505
That's ridiculous.

805
01:03:54,512 --> 01:03:59,363
Never even heard of these people,
and that was two decades ago.

806
01:04:01,502 --> 01:04:05,270
Fine, if my dad was so dangerous,
then why didn't you ever arrest him?

807
01:04:06,158 --> 01:04:07,910
No evidence.

808
01:04:08,511 --> 01:04:11,815
We didn't even have sufficient
cause for a search warrant.

809
01:04:11,915 --> 01:04:16,036
Asked for my professional opinion,
and I told you.

810
01:04:16,136 --> 01:04:19,339
Kat, that's just what I think.

811
01:04:19,439 --> 01:04:20,889
Which is?

812
01:04:23,526 --> 01:04:27,460
I think you father caught your mother
fucking her boyfriend and he killed her.

813
01:04:28,863 --> 01:04:31,431
Well, then what did he do with the body?

814
01:04:34,051 --> 01:04:36,269
That's a damn mystery.

815
01:04:49,235 --> 01:04:50,769
Kat.

816
01:04:51,901 --> 01:04:54,841
Come on. Where are you going?

817
01:04:54,941 --> 01:04:57,542
You know what I think, Detective?

818
01:04:58,293 --> 01:05:00,660
I think you're full of shit.

819
01:05:18,098 --> 01:05:20,350
Come on, strong man.
You can do better than that.

820
01:05:21,072 --> 01:05:22,818
What, like this?

821
01:05:23,119 --> 01:05:26,387
No. Harder.

822
01:05:26,990 --> 01:05:29,820
Put those muscles to
good used for a change.

823
01:05:29,920 --> 01:05:33,149
That's better. That's it.
Come on, give it a whack.

824
01:05:40,637 --> 01:05:42,350
You're already here?

825
01:05:43,259 --> 01:05:47,043
Yeah. I was just helping
your mom with dinner.

826
01:05:47,143 --> 01:05:49,094
Unlike some people.

827
01:06:05,545 --> 01:06:09,399
Hi, Mrs. Hillman. It's Kat.
I'm sorry, were you in bed?

828
01:06:09,499 --> 01:06:13,002
Oh, oh, no. I... I was just lying down.

829
01:06:13,102 --> 01:06:15,872
I... I haven't been feeling well.

830
01:06:16,222 --> 01:06:18,758
Well, I'm sorry to bother you.
But... is Phil here?

831
01:06:18,858 --> 01:06:20,960
No. He isn't.

832
01:06:21,060 --> 01:06:22,833
Do you know where he is?

833
01:06:22,933 --> 01:06:26,427
I'm afraid not. That boy
sometimes goes out gallivanting

834
01:06:26,527 --> 01:06:29,437
'til all hours of the night.

835
01:06:29,786 --> 01:06:32,171
Okay, well, could you please tell him
to call me as soon as he gets home?

836
01:06:32,271 --> 01:06:35,041
- It's kind of important.
- Of course.

837
01:06:35,141 --> 01:06:37,677
Thank you.
Sorry again for bothering you.

838
01:06:37,777 --> 01:06:40,785
Oh, it's... it's no problem.

839
01:06:41,264 --> 01:06:43,765
- Goodnight, dear.
- Good night.

840
01:07:03,803 --> 01:07:05,889
I don't think it's right with her here.

841
01:07:06,089 --> 01:07:10,685
- But if Kat says she's comfortable, I don't...
- I don't care what Kat said.

842
01:07:11,310 --> 01:07:12,776
Dad?

843
01:07:13,146 --> 01:07:14,803
Honey?

844
01:07:16,078 --> 01:07:18,334
I'm sorry. I didn't mean to wake you.

845
01:07:18,434 --> 01:07:23,855
If you two are arguing over whether or
not May can sleep over, it's totally fine.

846
01:07:23,956 --> 01:07:27,801
- Sweetheart, I don't think...
- No, no, no, dad, seriously. I don't mind.

847
01:07:28,094 --> 01:07:31,196
Well, you're sick, and we have to
get you to the airport tomorrow.

848
01:07:31,647 --> 01:07:34,597
I'm almost better.
My flight's not until the afternoon.

849
01:07:36,052 --> 01:07:39,321
You know what, this is my house
and I call the shots around here.

850
01:07:45,561 --> 01:07:47,445
Sorry, Kat.

851
01:07:48,147 --> 01:07:51,249
I didn't mean for you
to get dragged into this.

852
01:07:56,972 --> 01:07:59,742
To Phil, may he rest in pieces.

853
01:08:00,432 --> 01:08:02,625
Oh, my God.

854
01:08:03,994 --> 01:08:05,460
No, fuck Phil.

855
01:08:05,560 --> 01:08:09,252
Seriously, fuck him.
The jerk never even called me back.

856
01:08:09,352 --> 01:08:12,121
That's the spirit. Fuck Phil.

857
01:08:12,221 --> 01:08:14,971
Or, rather, don't fuck Phil.
Stop fucking Phil.

858
01:08:15,071 --> 01:08:18,678
Yeah. Fuck that hot stud cop instead.

859
01:08:18,778 --> 01:08:21,744
Done and done.

860
01:08:23,130 --> 01:08:25,485
You know, he said something
kind of weird the other night.

861
01:08:25,585 --> 01:08:30,001
What'd he say? "I'm gonna plough
you 'til you can't walk straight"?

862
01:08:31,291 --> 01:08:32,956
No.

863
01:08:34,241 --> 01:08:35,776
Yeah, it was so...

864
01:08:35,876 --> 01:08:40,949
He said that he thinks
my dad killed my mother.

865
01:08:44,687 --> 01:08:46,288
What?

866
01:08:49,675 --> 01:08:51,126
What?

867
01:08:52,327 --> 01:08:56,833
I... I told you that, Kat. Ages ago.

868
01:08:57,033 --> 01:08:58,433
We both did.

869
01:08:59,184 --> 01:09:00,587
What are you talking about?

870
01:09:00,687 --> 01:09:02,229
It was right after your mom disappeared,

871
01:09:02,329 --> 01:09:05,558
and you just didn't
seem to want to hear it.

872
01:09:05,658 --> 01:09:09,879
Remember? I asked if maybe
your dad had something to hide?

873
01:09:09,979 --> 01:09:14,482
You just blew it off. You said he was
too transparent to hide anything.

874
01:09:18,588 --> 01:09:20,856
You guys are fucking crazy.

875
01:09:23,576 --> 01:09:25,979
Yeah. Forget it.

876
01:09:26,079 --> 01:09:28,448
We both watch way too much bad TV.

877
01:09:28,548 --> 01:09:31,098
But that's why you love us, right?

878
01:09:34,558 --> 01:09:37,874
God, there's nothing more disgusting
than warm, flat champagne.

879
01:09:37,974 --> 01:09:39,876
- Here, give me that.
- What?

880
01:09:39,976 --> 01:09:42,095
The bottle, please.

881
01:09:44,761 --> 01:09:48,334
- What are you doing?
- It's a trick I learned at school.

882
01:09:48,434 --> 01:09:50,753
You put the bottle in the
freezer for a few minutes,

883
01:09:50,853 --> 01:09:55,168
and it is chilled to perfection.
Come and help me.

884
01:10:04,801 --> 01:10:07,107
- Mickey?
- There's no way that I am moving

885
01:10:07,207 --> 01:10:10,573
a bunch of old, mouldy newspapers.
Fuck that.

886
01:10:10,673 --> 01:10:13,606
Get your skinny gay ass over here.

887
01:10:17,095 --> 01:10:19,013
Get that one.

888
01:10:25,538 --> 01:10:27,323
It's stuck.

889
01:10:27,774 --> 01:10:29,405
What the...

890
01:10:31,475 --> 01:10:34,043
Why would you lock a fucking freezer?

891
01:10:34,764 --> 01:10:37,118
What the hell is going on down here?

892
01:10:37,483 --> 01:10:42,019
Nothing. We're just talking,
and drinking champagne.

893
01:10:44,907 --> 01:10:47,193
Well, it's time for
your friends to leave.

894
01:10:47,293 --> 01:10:49,128
What are you talking about?

895
01:10:50,079 --> 01:10:52,165
You heard me, Kat. The party is over.

896
01:10:52,265 --> 01:10:53,996
Are you joking?

897
01:10:54,684 --> 01:10:56,986
Dad, I hate to break it to you,
but I'm a fuckin' adult.

898
01:10:57,086 --> 01:10:59,322
You can't tell me what to do.

899
01:10:59,472 --> 01:11:01,474
When you're under my roof,
you will do as I say.

900
01:11:01,574 --> 01:11:04,661
And I'm saying your friends
need to go home, now.

901
01:11:04,761 --> 01:11:08,298
- Oh, my God. What is your problem?
- Cool it. It's... it's okay, Kat.

902
01:11:08,398 --> 01:11:10,566
- Yeah. Don't worry about it.
- No...

903
01:11:10,666 --> 01:11:12,801
Goodnight, Mr. Connors.

904
01:11:13,052 --> 01:11:15,270
Wait, I'll walk you guys out.

905
01:11:29,202 --> 01:11:32,703
Thank you for completely humiliating
me in front of my friends.

906
01:11:32,989 --> 01:11:36,123
So fucking glad I'm getting
out of here tomorrow.

907
01:11:40,520 --> 01:11:42,932
Sorry my dad is being such a douche.

908
01:11:43,032 --> 01:11:45,668
Whatever. I gotta fly out
early tomorrow anyway.

909
01:11:45,768 --> 01:11:49,489
- Me too, and I'm not even packed yet.
- Sure you're okay to drive?

910
01:11:49,589 --> 01:11:52,010
Unlike you lightweights,
I can handle my liquor.

911
01:11:55,545 --> 01:11:59,298
- God, I'm gonna miss you guys.
- Oh, my God, drama queen.

912
01:11:59,398 --> 01:12:02,086
It'll be summer soon, and we'll
be back in this rancid hellhole

913
01:12:02,186 --> 01:12:04,812
for three freakin' months.

914
01:12:06,455 --> 01:12:10,326
I know. Yeah, well, take care.
Don't forget to write.

915
01:12:10,426 --> 01:12:13,228
Yeah. You too, shithead.

916
01:12:13,529 --> 01:12:16,565
- Bye, Kat. Have a safe flight, all right?
- You too.

917
01:13:00,176 --> 01:13:01,649
Hey.

918
01:13:04,880 --> 01:13:06,372
Hey.

919
01:13:06,472 --> 01:13:08,449
Are you all right?

920
01:13:08,549 --> 01:13:11,649
- You look drunk.
- Oh, yeah?

921
01:13:11,799 --> 01:13:14,022
Look who's talking.

922
01:13:16,842 --> 01:13:19,709
So you've been avoiding
me on purpose, or what?

923
01:13:21,862 --> 01:13:25,463
- What do you mean?
- I came by your house last week.

924
01:13:25,768 --> 01:13:28,104
Told your mother that
I needed to talk to you.

925
01:13:28,204 --> 01:13:29,777
Really?

926
01:13:31,454 --> 01:13:33,551
I didn't get the message.

927
01:13:34,041 --> 01:13:36,325
What did you want to talk to me about?

928
01:13:38,179 --> 01:13:41,046
Just been thinking
about a lot of things.

929
01:13:42,866 --> 01:13:45,344
You know, I feel like after...

930
01:13:45,653 --> 01:13:48,574
my mother left,
everything changed between us.

931
01:13:48,874 --> 01:13:52,275
We were different. You were different.

932
01:13:54,328 --> 01:13:57,083
Everything was different after that.

933
01:13:57,183 --> 01:14:01,111
Phil, where were you that day?
You were supposed to pick me up from school.

934
01:14:02,420 --> 01:14:06,337
I told you. I was at Thomas'.

935
01:14:07,558 --> 01:14:10,012
My God, don't you get it?

936
01:14:10,112 --> 01:14:12,415
It doesn't matter anymore.
You don't have to lie.

937
01:14:12,865 --> 01:14:15,568
What do you mean?
What makes you think that I'm lying?

938
01:14:15,668 --> 01:14:17,437
Okay, I'm not accusing you of lying.

939
01:14:17,537 --> 01:14:21,789
All I'm saying is whatever it is that
you know, you can just tell me.

940
01:14:29,065 --> 01:14:33,609
You know what? What we had was sweet,
and cute, and great and everything, but...

941
01:14:33,959 --> 01:14:35,737
I think we both know that it's over.

942
01:14:36,538 --> 01:14:37,755
It's in the past,

943
01:14:37,855 --> 01:14:41,591
and I need to know what happened that
day so that I can move on with my life.

944
01:14:42,494 --> 01:14:45,878
Please, Phil, I'm not gonna get
mad at you. I just want to know.

945
01:14:47,648 --> 01:14:51,215
I told you. I don't know anything.

946
01:14:53,037 --> 01:14:55,954
Was there something going on
between you and my mother?

947
01:14:58,741 --> 01:15:01,719
- What?
- You heard me. Were you fucking my mom?

948
01:15:01,819 --> 01:15:05,217
- Because some people think that you were.
- What... what... what people?

949
01:15:05,517 --> 01:15:09,455
Kat, you're... you're drunk. And crazy.

950
01:15:09,555 --> 01:15:13,283
Phil, I just need to know!
Please, I don't care what it is.

951
01:15:13,383 --> 01:15:18,411
I just cannot keep living my life in the
dark just, like, fucking wondering!

952
01:15:21,650 --> 01:15:23,835
I can't help you, Kat.

953
01:15:29,442 --> 01:15:31,059
I'm sorry.

954
01:15:45,691 --> 01:15:48,053
But I will tell you one thing.

955
01:15:49,610 --> 01:15:51,967
Your dad knows where she is.

956
01:15:52,248 --> 01:15:54,566
He's been keeping her up
his sleeve this whole time.

957
01:15:57,820 --> 01:15:59,286
What do you mean?

958
01:16:01,521 --> 01:16:03,528
Don't ask me.

959
01:16:04,805 --> 01:16:06,738
Ask him.

960
01:17:04,904 --> 01:17:06,846
Kat!

961
01:17:07,296 --> 01:17:10,735
Kat! I'm up here!

962
01:17:12,777 --> 01:17:14,762
Over here!

963
01:17:15,955 --> 01:17:18,996
No! This way!

964
01:17:19,502 --> 01:17:23,161
Yes! Right in front of you!

965
01:17:24,539 --> 01:17:27,040
I'm right here, Kat.

