01:17:30,579 --> 01:17:32,536
Help me!

967
01:17:32,915 --> 01:17:36,684
Please! Help me, Kat!

968
01:17:39,288 --> 01:17:41,618
Help me!

969
01:19:58,544 --> 01:19:59,848
Kat!

970
01:20:02,328 --> 01:20:03,980
What are you doing?

971
01:20:09,171 --> 01:20:10,839
Dad?

972
01:20:13,256 --> 01:20:15,707
Do you know where mom is?

973
01:20:28,590 --> 01:20:30,291
What?

974
01:20:30,992 --> 01:20:33,558
Do you know where mom is?

975
01:20:34,512 --> 01:20:37,294
Because Phil says that you do.

976
01:20:39,749 --> 01:20:43,667
Phil? Your stoner boyfriend
who can't keep a job?

977
01:20:55,483 --> 01:20:58,352
The answer is no, I don't.

978
01:21:05,677 --> 01:21:07,852
Anything else?

979
01:21:18,774 --> 01:21:23,111
Well, clean up this mess. We have to
get you to the airport in a few hours.

980
01:21:28,934 --> 01:21:29,720
Dad?

981
01:21:35,174 --> 01:21:37,492
I'm sorry.

982
01:21:40,646 --> 01:21:42,419
It's all right.

983
01:22:25,874 --> 01:22:29,211
So make sure to call so I know
that you landed all right.

984
01:22:29,311 --> 01:22:30,747
Okay.

985
01:22:33,696 --> 01:22:36,531
So see you in a couple of months?

986
01:22:54,453 --> 01:22:56,537
I love you, baby.

987
01:23:02,995 --> 01:23:04,948
I love you too.

988
01:23:12,721 --> 01:23:15,393
I should probably board.

989
01:23:20,879 --> 01:23:22,732
See you.

990
01:23:29,271 --> 01:23:31,197
Goodbye, sweetheart.

991
01:24:06,058 --> 01:24:08,794
<i>That was the last time I saw my father.</i>

992
01:24:08,894 --> 01:24:11,880
<i>It turns out Beth,
Mickey and Theo were right.</i>

993
01:24:11,980 --> 01:24:16,444
<i>A few weeks after I left,
my dad got shitfaced drunk in a bar,</i>

994
01:24:16,544 --> 01:24:19,142
<i>and confessed to killing my mother.</i>

995
01:24:21,137 --> 01:24:24,238
<i>He hung himself in his
jail cell with a sheet.</i>

996
01:24:25,994 --> 01:24:30,132
<i>Before he died, he revealed that my
mother's body was in the freezer,</i>

997
01:24:30,232 --> 01:24:33,768
<i>and that he'd taken it out during
the night while I was sleeping.</i>

998
01:24:34,019 --> 01:24:38,106
<i>He buried her up in the mountains.
Since it'd been frozen for so long,</i>

999
01:24:38,206 --> 01:24:43,111
<i>her corpse decomposed freakishly fast,
turning to liquid as it melted.</i>

1000
01:24:43,562 --> 01:24:47,448
<i>By the time they dug her up,
there was basically nothing left.</i>

1001
01:24:51,803 --> 01:24:54,806
<i>I was seventeen when
my mother disappeared.</i>

1002
01:24:55,307 --> 01:24:59,127
<i>Like, one day she was there,
cleaning, making dinner,</i>

1003
01:24:59,227 --> 01:25:01,144
<i>and the next...</i>

1004
01:25:02,524 --> 01:25:04,380
<i>she was gone.</i>

1005
01:26:20,275 --> 01:26:21,900
Stop it.

1006
01:26:31,069 --> 01:26:33,204
Evie, stop.

1007
01:26:39,211 --> 01:26:40,778
Evie.

1008
01:26:42,029 --> 01:26:43,679
Stop.

1009
01:26:51,840 --> 01:26:53,498
Please.

1010
01:26:56,325 --> 01:26:58,010
Evie.

1011
01:26:59,481 --> 01:27:01,630
Stop!

1012
01:27:04,920 --> 01:27:06,320
Stop.

1013
01:27:42,272 --> 01:27:44,618
<i>Because I never saw my mother again,</i>

1014
01:27:44,718 --> 01:27:47,353
<i>she remains in absence to me.</i>

1015
01:27:47,929 --> 01:27:50,001
<i>An empty space.</i>

1016
01:27:50,465 --> 01:27:53,688
<i>An invisible, half remembered ghost.</i>

1017
01:27:55,802 --> 01:28:00,709
<i>So even now I catch myself thinking
that I'm gonna run into her some day.</i>

1018
01:28:01,009 --> 01:28:04,379
<i>Like I'll be at a stop light,
and look over at the car next to me</i>

1019
01:28:04,479 --> 01:28:08,678
<i>and there she'll be,
scowling at me with disapproval.</i>

1020
01:28:09,051 --> 01:28:12,487
<i>Or I'll spot her across some
crowded street, or train station,</i>

1021
01:28:12,587 --> 01:28:17,639
<i>and we'll run toward each other like
one of those cheesy TV movies.</i>

1022
01:28:18,608 --> 01:28:21,592
<i>She'll hug me like a long, lost lover,</i>

1023
01:28:22,397 --> 01:28:25,312
<i>then take my face in her long,</i>

1024
01:28:25,600 --> 01:28:27,697
<i>graceful hands,</i>

1025
01:28:28,320 --> 01:28:30,988
<i>look me in the eyes and say...</i>

1026
01:28:34,576 --> 01:28:36,641
<i>"I'm here, Kat.</i>

1027
01:28:38,161 --> 01:28:39,974
<i>I'm here."</i>

